  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this letter, William Lloyd Garrison discusses the controversy regarding the Sabbath and the &quot;Call for a Convention to protest against penal legislation in favor of a Sabbatical observance, and to explode a mischievous delusion everywhere prevailing, that one day in the week is more holy than another---that we are to give one-seventh portion of our time to God, and the rest we may devote to &apos;secular&apos; matters!&quot; William Lloyd Garrison considers it &quot;one of the great reformatory movements of the age.&quot; He lists the titles and authors of the ten projected essays on the Sabbath question that will be discussed and presented at the convention. He comments on the &quot;Sabbatical operations&quot; by the Free Church in Scotland and Dr. Candlish. He acknowledges the gift of $50 made by Edward Morris Davis towards the anti-Sabbath convention.</subfield>
  </datafield>
